s%20grows.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBroken%20down%20by%20source%2C%20it%20sees%20oil%20and%20gas%20accounting%20for%2054%25%20of%20the%20global%20energy%20mix%20by%202050%2C%20coal%20at%2013%25%2C%20nuclear%20energy%20at%206%25%2C%20bioenergy%20at%2010%25%2C%20and%20renewables%20like%20wind%2C%20solar%2C%20and%20hydroelectric%20at%2015%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20forecast%20stands%20in%20contrast%20to%20predictions%20from%20the%20International%20Energy%20Agency%2C%20which%20predicts%20that%20oil%20and%20gas%20demand%20will%20peak%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fcommodities%2Fglobal-oil-demand-prices-supply-opec-us-crude-producers-iea-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eplateau%20at%20105.6%20million%20barrels%20per%20day%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%202029.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EExxon%2C%20the%20leading%20oil%20and%20gas%20company%20in%20the%20US%2C%20pointed%20to%20a%20rise%20in%20the%20global%20population%20to%2010%20billion%20in%202050%2C%20up%20from%208%20billion%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20half%20of%20the%20world's%20population%20currently%20living%20below%20Exxon's%20%26quot%3Bmodern%20energy%20minimum%26quot%3B%E2%80%94having%20enough%20energy%20for%20housing%2C%20infrastructure%2C%20jobs%2C%20and%20mobility%E2%80%94the%20company%20projects%20a%2015%25%20increase%20in%20global%20energy%20use%20is%20necessary%20for%20reliable%20energy%20worldwide%20by%202050.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20rise%20in%20energy%20use%20will%20be%20predominantly%20driven%20by%20a%2025%25%20increase%20among%20developing%20countries%2C%20whose%20current%20energy%20problems%20put%20inhabitants%20at%20risk%20from%20harmful%20cooking%20fuels%2C%20limited%20electricity%2C%20and%20poverty%2C%20the%20report%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDeveloped%20countries%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20will%20decrease%20energy%20use%20by%2010%25%20due%20to%20improved%20efficiency.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20says%20that%20even%20greater%20adoption%20of%20electric%20vehicles%20won't%20make%20a%20dent%20in%20oil%20and%20gas%20usage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20many%20don't%20realize%20is%20that%20making%20gasoline%20is%20but%20one%20relatively%20small%20use%20for%20oil%2C%26quot%3B%20Exxon%20said%20in%20its%20report%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20majority%20of%20the%20world's%20oil%20is%20used%20for%20industrial%20processes%20like%20manufacturing%2C%20and%20for%20transportation%20like%20shipping%2C%20trucking%2C%20and%20air%20travel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20services%20are%20needed%20for%20modern%20life%20%E2%80%93%20and%20they%20also%20fuel%20future%20economic%20growth%20in%20the%20developing%20world%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20report%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20the%20report%20predicts%20carbon%20emissions%20will%20drop%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%202030.%20Last%20year%2C%20the%20company's%20annual%20report%20said%20the%20world%20likely%20won't%20meet%20the%20emission%20reduction%20targets%20that%20were%20set%20in%20the%20Paris%20Climate%20Accords%20in%202015%20to%20curb%20the%20effects%20of%20climate%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Foil-demand-peak-exxon-gas-energy-carbon-emissions-renewable-energy-2024-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1724698618000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66cccfd243b5e59d16b55f6b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fcommodities%2Foil-demand-peak-exxon-gas-energy-carbon-emissions-renewable-energy-2024-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Exxon%20says%20oil%20and%20gas%20use%20will%20remain%20high%20until%20the%20middle%20of%20this%20century%2C%20as%20the%20world%20population%20hits%2010%20billion%20people%20and%20energy%20needs%20grow.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22kcloonan%40insider.com%20(Kelly%20Cloonan)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A142%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider