with%20law%20enforcement.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDurov%20himself%20has%20yet%20to%20be%20charged.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Sunday%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Ftelegram-messaging-app-ceo-pavel-durov-arrested-france-tf1-tv-says-2024-08-24%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EReuters%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20citing%20a%20French%20police%20source%2C%20said%20that%20Durov%20%26quot%3Bwas%20arrested%20as%20part%20of%20a%20preliminary%20police%20investigation%20into%20allegedly%20allowing%20a%20wide%20range%20of%20crimes%20due%20to%20a%20lack%20of%20moderators%20on%20Telegram%20and%20a%20lack%20of%20cooperation%20with%20police.%26quot%3B%20The%20Times%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2024%2F08%2F25%2Ftechnology%2Fpavel-durov-telegram-detained-france.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Especulated%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20%26quot%3BFrench%20authorities%20may%20try%20to%20force%20Telegram%20to%20share%20information%20with%20them%20on%20criminal%20channels%20that%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20are%20used%20to%20sell%20firearms%20or%20coordinate%20terrorist%20attacks.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20have%20also%20been%20unconfirmed%20suspicions%20that%20Durov's%20arrest%20had%20something%20to%20do%20with%20strained%20relations%20between%20France%20and%20Russia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDurov%2C%20who%20lives%20in%20Dubai%2C%20is%20a%20Russian%20citizen.%20And%20while%20he%20has%20said%20he%20started%20Telegram%20because%20of%20a%20dispute%20with%20Russian%20authorities%2C%20the%20government%20there%20has%20allowed%20Telegram%20to%20stay%20in%20business%20while%20it%20has%20blocked%20other%20social-media%20services%20like%20Facebook%20and%20Twitter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20led%20observers%20like%20Ben%20Thompson%2C%20a%20tech%20analyst%2C%20to%20float%20the%20possibility%20that%20Durov's%20arrest%20is%20%26quot%3Bon%20the%20level%20of%20espionage%20and%20spycraft.%26quot%3B%20On%20Monday%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftelegram-standing-behind-its-ceo-after-his-arrest-in-paris-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFrench%20President%20Emmanuel%20Macron%3C%2Fa%3E%20insisted%20this%20was%20not%20the%20case%2C%20saying%20the%20arrest%20was%20part%20of%20an%20%26quot%3Bongoing%20judicial%20investigation%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20%26quot%3Bthis%20is%20in%20no%20way%20a%20political%20decision.%26quot%3B%20He%20added%3A%20%26quot%3BIt%20is%20up%20to%20the%20judges%20to%20decide.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225b620418-0f0a-40b1-bded-b0a7acbd57c3%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20is%20this%20such%20a%20big%20deal%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20obvious%20reason%20is%20that%20we%20haven't%20seen%20someone%20who%20runs%20a%20big%20social-media%20platform%20arrested%20when%20traveling%20abroad%20before.%20Picture%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmark-zuckerberg%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMark%20Zuckerberg%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20Elon%20Musk%20getting%20tossed%20in%20jail%20after%20stepping%20off%20their%20private%20planes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20said%2C%20people%20who%20run%20tech%20companies%20with%20global%20reach%20%E2%80%94%20generally%2C%20Americans%20who%20live%20in%20America%20%E2%80%94%20have%20for%20quite%20some%20time%20been%20dealing%20with%20the%20fact%20that%20different%20countries%20have%20different%20rules%20about%20tech%20and%20the%20internet.%20And%20the%20way%20they've%20dealt%20with%20those%20differences%20is%20by%20accepting%20the%20rules%20of%20the%20road%20in%20the%20countries%20where%20they%20operate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20why%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftim-cook-leaked-apple-memo-explains-hkmap-live-app-removal-2019-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EApple%20took%20down%20an%20app%3C%2Fa%3E%20used%20by%20Hong%20Kong%20protesters%20in%202019%2C%20after%20China%20complained.%20And%20it's%20why%20Netflix%20took%20down%20an%20episode%20of%20